{"repo": "DevilXD/TwitchDropsMiner", "pull_number": 734, "instance_id": "DevilXD__TwitchDropsMiner-734", "issue_numbers": [732], "base_commit": "7116cbc759e200753e9c4df335c2edb54854480a", "patch": "diff --git a/.github/workflows/ci.yml b/.github/workflows/ci.yml\nindex d93894408..517577ad6 100644\n--- a/.github/workflows/ci.yml\n+++ b/.github/workflows/ci.yml\n@@ -103,8 +103,16 @@ jobs:\n           path: Twitch.Drops.Miner.Windows.zip\n \n   linux-pyinstaller:\n-    name: Linux (PyInstaller)\n-    runs-on: ubuntu-22.04\n+    name: Linux (PyInstaller) (${{matrix.arch}})\n+    strategy:\n+      fail-fast: false\n+      matrix:\n+        include:\n+          - arch: x86_64\n+            runner: ubuntu-22.04\n+          - arch: aarch64\n+            runner: ubuntu-22.04-arm\n+    runs-on: ${{matrix.runner}}\n     needs:\n       - validate\n \n@@ -146,7 +154,8 @@ jobs:\n         run: |\n           mkdir -p /tmp/libXft\n           cd /tmp/libXft\n-          curl -L https://xorg.freedesktop.org/releases/individual/lib/libXft-2.3.8.tar.xz -o libXft.tar.xz\n+          curl -fL https://xorg.freedesktop.org/releases/individual/lib/libXft-2.3.9.tar.xz -o libXft.tar.xz\n+          sha256sum libXft.tar.xz\n           tar xvf libXft.tar.xz\n           cd libXft-*\n           ./configure --prefix=/tmp/libXft --sysconfdir=/etc --disable-static\n@@ -166,18 +175,26 @@ jobs:\n           folder='Twitch Drops Miner'\n           mkdir \"${folder}\"\n           cp manual.txt dist/* \"${folder}\"\n-          7z a Twitch.Drops.Miner.Linux.PyInstaller.zip \"${folder}\"\n+          7z a 'Twitch.Drops.Miner.Linux.PyInstaller-${{matrix.arch}}.zip' \"${folder}\"\n \n       - name: Upload build artifact\n         uses: actions/upload-artifact@v4\n         with:\n           if-no-files-found: error\n-          name: Twitch.Drops.Miner.Linux.PyInstaller\n-          path: Twitch.Drops.Miner.Linux.PyInstaller.zip\n+          name: Twitch.Drops.Miner.Linux.PyInstaller-${{matrix.arch}}\n+          path: Twitch.Drops.Miner.Linux.PyInstaller-${{matrix.arch}}.zip\n \n   linux-appimage:\n-    name: Linux (AppImage)\n-    runs-on: ubuntu-22.04\n+    name: Linux (AppImage) (${{matrix.arch}})\n+    strategy:\n+      fail-fast: false\n+      matrix:\n+        include:\n+          - arch: x86_64\n+            runner: ubuntu-22.04\n+          - arch: aarch64\n+            runner: ubuntu-22.04-arm\n+    runs-on: ${{matrix.runner}}\n     needs:\n       - validate\n \n@@ -207,7 +224,8 @@ jobs:\n \n       - name: Create AppImage\n         env:\n-          ARCH: x86_64\n+          ARCH: ${{matrix.arch}}\n+          ARCH_APT: ${{matrix.arch == 'x86_64' && 'amd64' || 'arm64'}}\n           APP_VERSION: ${{steps.vars.outputs.app_version}}.${{steps.vars.outputs.sha_short}}\n           PYTHON_VERSION: ${{env.PYTHON_VERSION}}\n         run: |\n@@ -218,14 +236,14 @@ jobs:\n           folder='Twitch Drops Miner'\n           mkdir \"${folder}\"\n           cp *.AppImage manual.txt \"${folder}\"\n-          7z a Twitch.Drops.Miner.Linux.AppImage.zip \"${folder}\"\n+          7z a 'Twitch.Drops.Miner.Linux.AppImage-${{matrix.arch}}.zip' \"${folder}\"\n \n       - name: Upload build artifact\n         uses: actions/upload-artifact@v4\n         with:\n           if-no-files-found: error\n-          name: Twitch.Drops.Miner.Linux.AppImage\n-          path: Twitch.Drops.Miner.Linux.AppImage.zip\n+          name: Twitch.Drops.Miner.Linux.AppImage-${{matrix.arch}}\n+          path: Twitch.Drops.Miner.Linux.AppImage-${{matrix.arch}}.zip\n \n   update_releases_page:\n     name: Upload builds to Releases\ndiff --git a/appimage/AppImageBuilder.yml b/appimage/AppImageBuilder.yml\nindex 2b555b346..68b9f282b 100644\n--- a/appimage/AppImageBuilder.yml\n+++ b/appimage/AppImageBuilder.yml\n@@ -43,11 +43,15 @@ AppDir:\n     exec_args: '${APPDIR}/usr/src/main.py $@'\n \n   apt:\n-    arch: amd64\n+    arch:\n+      - '{{ARCH_APT}}'\n     sources:\n-      - sourceline: deb http://archive.ubuntu.com/ubuntu/ jammy main\n-      - sourceline: deb http://archive.ubuntu.com/ubuntu/ jammy-updates main\n-      - sourceline: deb http://archive.ubuntu.com/ubuntu/ jammy-security main\n+      - sourceline: deb [arch=amd64] http://archive.ubuntu.com/ubuntu/ jammy main\n+      - sourceline: deb [arch=amd64] http://archive.ubuntu.com/ubuntu/ jammy-updates main\n+      - sourceline: deb [arch=amd64] http://archive.ubuntu.com/ubuntu/ jammy-security main\n+      - sourceline: deb [arch=arm64] http://ports.ubuntu.com/ubuntu-ports/ jammy main\n+      - sourceline: deb [arch=arm64] http://ports.ubuntu.com/ubuntu-ports/ jammy-updates main\n+      - sourceline: deb [arch=arm64] http://ports.ubuntu.com/ubuntu-ports/ jammy-security main\n         key_url: http://keyserver.ubuntu.com/pks/lookup?op=get&search=0x871920D1991BC93C\n \n     include:\n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "Provide aarch64 builds for Linux\nHey, @DevilXD\n\nI was wondering if you would be in favor of providing ARM64 dev builds for Linux (PyInstaller and AppImage packages), since GitHub has been giving us ARM runners for free for quite some time now...\n\nAt the very least, I think it's fair to say that user interest exists:\n\n- https://github.com/DevilXD/TwitchDropsMiner/issues/221\n- https://github.com/DevilXD/TwitchDropsMiner/issues/244\n- https://github.com/DevilXD/TwitchDropsMiner/issues/348\n- https://github.com/DevilXD/TwitchDropsMiner/issues/397\n- https://github.com/DevilXD/TwitchDropsMiner/issues/413\n- https://github.com/DevilXD/TwitchDropsMiner/issues/588\n\nI personally don't own any ARM64 device, but I've been experimenting with a local aarch64 build that is running via emulation quite nicely with QEMU!\n\nI should also point out that having these builds wouldn't change the current [Linux requirements](https://github.com/DevilXD/TwitchDropsMiner?tab=readme-ov-file#notes-about-the-linux-build) in any way.\n\nLet me know what you think!\n\n", "hints_text": "\n\n", "all_hints_text": "Hello,\n\nI mean, sure, if you'd like to add it and it's possible, I'd say go for it :)\n\nI fear the Tkinter dependencies will be hard to get around with, as they were on other Linux versions. Or won't they?\n>I mean, sure, if you'd like to add it and it's possible, I'd say go for it :)\n\nAlright, cool :)\n\nBut first I'll finish the work of moving the AppImage to the new runtime.\n\n>I fear the Tkinter dependencies will be hard to get around with, as they were on other Linux versions. Or won't they?\n\nNot at all, thankfully. Ubuntu itself builds and packages Tk for [many CPU architectures](https://packages.ubuntu.com/jammy/python3-tk#pdownload), so all the packaging tools have to do is find the aarch64-specific files (which I've already tested, and they do). \n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/DevilXD/TwitchDropsMiner/commit/1bdd6ad1f05af83a62995fb5522d2c6c7470de3c", "https://github.com/DevilXD/TwitchDropsMiner/commit/91b71ef9decf0c5b4f43b0c015c1c52b9b97e8ec"], "created_at": "2025-07-26T21:59:49Z"}
{"repo": "DevilXD/TwitchDropsMiner", "pull_number": 948, "instance_id": "DevilXD__TwitchDropsMiner-948", "issue_numbers": [932], "base_commit": "3b98b4b02cc7ea3bca9cff244ca671b11ae5e59d", "patch": "diff --git a/gui.py b/gui.py\nindex c4abdaf1e..0945f4f2c 100644\n--- a/gui.py\n+++ b/gui.py\n@@ -2391,6 +2391,28 @@ def print(self, message: str):\n         # print to our custom output\n         self.output.print(message)\n \n+    def _set_title_bar_color(self, color: int) -> None:\n+        \"\"\"\n+        Set the Windows title bar color to match the theme.\n+        Only works on Windows with DWM enabled.\n+\n+        Args:\n+            color: ARGB color value (e.g., 0x001E1E1E for dark gray).\n+        \"\"\"\n+        if sys.platform != \"win32\":\n+            return\n+        # DWMWA_CAPTION_COLOR = 35\n+        DWMWA_CAPTION_COLOR = 35\n+        hwnd = self._root.winfo_id()\n+        frame_hwnd = ctypes.windll.user32.GetParent(hwnd)\n+        color_value = ctypes.c_int(color)\n+        ctypes.windll.dwmapi.DwmSetWindowAttribute(\n+            frame_hwnd,\n+            DWMWA_CAPTION_COLOR,\n+            ctypes.byref(color_value),\n+            ctypes.sizeof(ctypes.c_int),\n+        )\n+\n     def apply_theme(self, dark: bool) -> None:\n         \"\"\"\n         Apply dark/light palette to ttk styles and Tk widgets in a minimal, non-invasive way.\n@@ -2579,6 +2601,14 @@ def apply_theme(self, dark: bool) -> None:\n         ):\n             self._root.option_add(key, sel_fg)\n \n+        # Set Windows title bar color to match dark theme\n+        if dark:\n+            # Use dark gray color 0x001E1E1E (ARGB format, matches bg color #1e1e1e)\n+            self._set_title_bar_color(0x001E1E1E)\n+        else:\n+            # Reset to system default title bar color\n+            self._set_title_bar_color(0xFFFFFFFF)\n+\n \n ###################\n # GUI MANAGER END #\n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "Match title bar color to the dark theme\nIf you're interested, use this to match the title bar color to the dark theme :\n\nwindll.dwmapi.DwmSetWindowAttribute(windll.user32.GetParent(window.winfo_id()), 35, byref(c_int(0x001E1E1E)), sizeof(c_int))\n", "hints_text": "Hello,\n\nThere's an entire UI rewrite planned in #690, so I'm not really interested in tinkering around the GUI more than is necessary, as it won't matter later anyway. The dark theme itself was quite an excessive addition already, but there was a PR submitted for it. If you want this to become part of the miner, please submit a PR for it as well.\nActually, lets keep this one open. Someone else might be interested in doing the PR instead.\n\n", "all_hints_text": "Hello,\n\nThere's an entire UI rewrite planned in #690, so I'm not really interested in tinkering around the GUI more than is necessary, as it won't matter later anyway. The dark theme itself was quite an excessive addition already, but there was a PR submitted for it. If you want this to become part of the miner, please submit a PR for it as well.\nActually, lets keep this one open. Someone else might be interested in doing the PR instead.\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/DevilXD/TwitchDropsMiner/commit/c0701b0f072aa80abcf1f2cc6fe1dc10284d7f7d", "https://github.com/DevilXD/TwitchDropsMiner/commit/d02a26b48f607bb0ebda90f174be07aa23386cfe"], "created_at": "2026-01-13T23:37:07Z"}
